name: Welcome and kick off meeting
description:
Welcome to GDG Cloud Baltimore. We'll have our first meeting to kick off the group. We'll provide an overview of Google Cloud Platform (GCP) and how it compares to competing cloud platform offerings.

We'll meet at the offices of Moser Consulting
17 Governors Court Windsor Mill, MD 21244

name: GDG Cloud Baltimore - December Meeting
description:
December GDG Cloud Baltimore Meeting.

The Google Cloud Baltimore Meetup is pleased to announce the agenda for an interactive introduction of Google Cloud, a set of solutions and products, including Google Cloud Platform and G Suite that can help you solve your toughest business challenges.

Together, we'll learn about:

1. One Cloud, endless possibilities (Compute, Storage, Data analytics, AL and Machine Learning and G Suite)
2. Digital Transformation of the Enterprise

You’ll actually use Google Cloud Platform during the meeting!

What you'll need:
1. Laptop / Chromebook
2. A Google account (if you don't have one, create one!)
3. A Google Cloud Platform Demo Account (Get a free $300 Google Cloud Platform credit - https://cloud.google.com/free/)

Prerequisites: None, this event is suitable for all skill and experience levels.

Refreshments and snacks will be provided.

name: GDG Cloud Baltimore - January 2019 Meeting - What makes GCP different?
description:
January 2019 GDG Cloud Baltimore Meeting.

Agenda: What makes Google Cloud Platform different?

We'll talk about:
1. Google-grade security
2. Global Network
3. Big Data
4. Billing by the second

Refreshments and snacks will be provided.

name: GDG Cloud Baltimore - February 2019 Meeting - Cloud Study Jam #1
description:
February 2019 GDG Cloud Baltimore Meeting.

Cloud Study Jam
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Kubernetes, Security, IoT on Cloud, and Machine Learning.

Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Agenda:
6:00pm: Welcome
6:05pm: Get free access to Qwiklabs
6:10 pm: Lab 1: Kubernetes Engine: Qwik Start
6:45 pm: Lab 2: App Dev: Deploying the Application into Kubernetes Engine - Java OR App Dev: Deploying the Application into Kubernetes Engine - Python
7:30 pm: Break
7:45 pm: Lab 3: Hello Istio with Kubernetes Engine
8:30 pm: Open Discussion: Kubernetes on Google Cloud
9:00pm: Event ends

Refreshments and snacks will be provided.
